      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><style>[data-colorid=ovcwdq5jgg]{color:#4269b8} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=ovcwdq5jgg]{color:#476ebd}[data-colorid=xidtxu74ag]{color:#4269b8} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=xidtxu74ag]{color:#476ebd}[data-colorid=seqh0rm4k4]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=seqh0rm4k4]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=l41cpzasvg]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=l41cpzasvg]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=fnn8v9stxc]{color:#4269b8} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=fnn8v9stxc]{color:#476ebd}[data-colorid=hfgqvruqpr]{color:#4269b8} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=hfgqvruqpr]{color:#476ebd}[data-colorid=rtcoo8twkm]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=rtcoo8twkm]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=u9b0k0odfh]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=u9b0k0odfh]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=xdutlapyp7]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=xdutlapyp7]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=arp1tpt608]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=arp1tpt608]{color:#4c9fc2}[data-colorid=tf179856y3]{color:#4269b8} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=tf179856y3]{color:#476ebd}[data-colorid=hin50gowmi]{color:#3d90b3} html[data-color-mode=dark] [data-colorid=hin50gowmi]{color:#4c9fc2}</style><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"1356\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Aces_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781733&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1356&amp;height=760\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Aces_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781733&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"718\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542236693\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_OCIO_Aces_Header.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542236678\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"5b758419-d05c-4281-b465-4e6ecb1d4445\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Aces_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781733&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1740&amp;height=976 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Aces_Header.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781733&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1356&amp;height=760 1x\" /></span><p><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">RenderMan features robust support for the industry-standard ACES color management system, and other color spaces, such as the popular Filmic Blender, in all bridge products, including the interactive RenderMan Image Tool.</span></p><h2 id=\"ColorManagement-OCIOConfigurations\">OCIO Configurations</h2><p>RenderMan ships with a number of OCIO configurations :</p><p /><p><strong><span data-colorid=\"u9b0k0odfh\">LINEAR-sRGB</span></strong><br />The original Sony Pictures Imageworks configuration has been used since the dawn of time.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Linear.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781949&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=600&amp;height=336\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Linear.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781949&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"561\" data-width=\"1000\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542236702\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_OCIO_Linear.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542236678\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"bc83b901-ab4d-40f2-b619-043c6ff03609\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Linear.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781949&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1000&amp;height=561 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Linear.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781949&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=600&amp;height=336 1x\" /></span><p /><p><strong><span data-colorid=\"seqh0rm4k4\">ACES-1.2</span></strong><br />The visual effects standard Academy Colour Encoding System for filmmaking and computer graphics.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Aces2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781948&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=600&amp;height=336\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Aces2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781948&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"718\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542236699\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_OCIO_Aces2.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542236678\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"b853128a-7904-4e1e-aa95-53f2b5d14f30\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Aces2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781948&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1200&amp;height=672 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_OCIO_Aces2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781948&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=600&amp;height=336 1x\" /></span><p /><p /><p><strong><span data-colorid=\"l41cpzasvg\">FILMIC BLENDER</span></strong><br />A popular BT.709-based configuration provides a high dynamic range and other effects typical in film stock. Developed by Troy Sobotka.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"600\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_Filmic_base.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781733&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=600&amp;height=335\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/542236678/RenderMan_Filmic_base.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781733&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"335\" data-width=\"600\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"542236690\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderMan_Filmic_base.gif\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/gif\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"542236678\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"0557347b-21d5-4550-87d7-3b58e6b23224\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_Filmic_base.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781733&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=600&amp;height=335 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/542236678/RenderMan_Filmic_base.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754330781733&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=600&amp;height=335 1x\" /></span><p /><h3 id=\"ColorManagement-Configurationselection\">Configuration selection</h3><ul><li><p><span data-colorid=\"hfgqvruqpr\">$OCIO</span>: Use the color space defined by your systems environment variable. Typically sRGB.</p></li><li><p><span data-colorid=\"xidtxu74ag\">Off</span>:&nbsp;&nbsp;Scene Linear is defined as the scene-wide color space.</p></li><li><p><span data-colorid=\"tf179856y3\">ACES1.2</span>: Use the ACES 1.2 color encoding system that ships with RenderMan 24.</p></li><li><p><span data-colorid=\"fnn8v9stxc\">Filmic Blender</span>: Use the popular BT.709 color space.</p></li><li><p><span data-colorid=\"ovcwdq5jgg\">Custom</span><span class=\"legacy-color-text-default\">: Allows for a custom color space file to be specified.</span><br /><br /></p></li></ul><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"8e1b18ac-a20d-4b83-a3a2-e32dd4bbe824\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>Please note that you will need to close and re-open IT when switching between OCIO configurations for the new color space to be correctly displayed in IT</p></div></div><h2 id=\"ColorManagement-Colormanageditems\">Color managed items</h2><ul><li><p><span data-colorid=\"arp1tpt608\">UI color values</span></p><ul><li><p>All DCC apps provide a color-managed color picker that will return a color in the rendering colorspace. RenderMan simply uses them as-is.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><span data-colorid=\"hin50gowmi\">Lights</span></p><ul><li><p>Color Temperature was computed in Rec.709 before 24.0 and is now color-managed.</p></li><li><p>PxrEnvDayLight is also color-managed and relies on the&nbsp;<strong>srgb_linear&nbsp;</strong>role.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><span data-colorid=\"rtcoo8twkm\">Textures</span></p><ul><li><p>Textures MUST be converted to the&nbsp;<strong>rendering</strong>&nbsp;color space before usage. This task can be accomplished by the Texture Manager.</p></li><li><p>It is also possible to use the PxrColorSpace pattern to convert a texture color, but at a performance cost.</p></li></ul></li><li><p><span data-colorid=\"xdutlapyp7\">Patterns</span></p><ul><li><p>PxrBlackBody is color-managed.</p></li><li><p>PxrHairColor is color-managed.</p></li><li><p>PxrColorSpace allows artists to convert from one color space to the&nbsp;<strong>rendering</strong>&nbsp;space.</p></li></ul></li></ul><p /><p /><p />"
    }
  },
